<paragraph blockId="24.[151,445,1390,1449]" box="[151,276,1425,1449]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<figureCitation box="[151,276,1425,1449]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 16" captionStart-1="FIGURE 17 a – e" captionStartId-0="25.[151,250,1283,1306]" captionStartId-1="26.[151,250,1733,1756]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,193,1261]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1428,193,1710]" captionTargetId-0="figure@25.[151,1436,193,1262]" captionTargetId-1="figure@26.[151,1436,193,1712]" captionTargetPageId-0="25" captionTargetPageId-1="26" captionText-0="FIGURE 16. Known distribution of Megachile rufoscopacea (black dot) and Megachile serrula (yellow triangle)." captionText-1="FIGURE 17 a – e. Megachile serrula. a. Female face. b. Female habitus. c. Male face. d. Male habitus. e. Male T 6 – T 7." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/246141/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/246142/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Figs 
<number box="[206,276,1425,1449]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="16.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="16.0">16–17</number>
</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1497,2025]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
This species is named for the small, evenly sized and spaced teeth on the male T 
<number box="[1049,1062,1497,1521]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="6.0">6</number>
which separate it from its congeners. It belongs to the species-group comprising 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName box="[692,863,1534,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ianthoptera">M. ianthoptera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[873,1012,1534,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulata">M. angulata</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1023,1161,1534,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seewaldi">M. seewaldi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1171,1297,1534,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorsata">M. dorsata</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1307,1436,1534,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Creightonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discolor">M. discolor</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[200,388,1569,1593]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufoscopacea">M. rufoscopacea</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1497,2025]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1605,1630]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Description.</emphasis>
Female. Vestiture, head, mesosoma and T 
<number box="[838,848,1605,1629]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
mostly pale yellowish–white, lower region of face orange, vertex and mesosomal dorsum black, basal segments of foreleg orange; T 
<number box="[1107,1121,1641,1665]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
–T 
<number box="[1153,1165,1641,1665]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="5.0">5</number>
black with short distal fringes, T 
<number box="[260,273,1677,1701]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="6.0">6</number>
black (
<figureCitation box="[355,479,1677,1701]" captionStart="FIGURE 17 a – e" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1733,1756]" captionTargetBox="[151,1428,193,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,193,1712]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 17 a – e. Megachile serrula. a. Female face. b. Female habitus. c. Male face. d. Male habitus. e. Male T 6 – T 7." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246142/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[407,434,1677,1701]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="17.0">17</number>
a–b
</figureCitation>
), scopa orange. Lengths: face 
<quantity box="[817,905,1677,1701]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
; scutum 
<quantity box="[1004,1092,1677,1701]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
; forewing 
<quantity box="[1211,1313,1677,1701]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="12.7">12.7 mm</quantity>
; body 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.52" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="15.2">15.2 mm</quantity>
. Structure. Clypeus a little wider than twice length, gently raised, densely punctuate, ventral edge straight (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 17 a – e" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1733,1756]" captionTargetBox="[151,1428,193,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,193,1712]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 17 a – e. Megachile serrula. a. Female face. b. Female habitus. c. Male face. d. Male habitus. e. Male T 6 – T 7." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246142/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,180,1749,1773]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="17.0">17</number>
a
</figureCitation>
); clypocellus: clypeus 
<number box="[450,461,1749,1773]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
: 
<number box="[465,509,1749,1773]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="0.7">0.7</number>
; scopal hairs slender and pointed distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1497,2025]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Male. Vestiture, gena, mesosoma venter and legs pale yellowish–white, face, upper mesepimeron, mesosomal dorsum and T 
<number box="[314,324,1821,1845]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
pale orange; T 
<number box="[499,512,1821,1845]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
–T 
<number box="[544,558,1821,1845]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="4.0">4</number>
black, pallid distal fringes, T 
<number box="[897,910,1821,1845]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="5.0">5</number>
orange, pallid distal fringe; T 
<number box="[1255,1268,1821,1845]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="6.0">6</number>
orange, naked (black) distally (
<figureCitation box="[337,461,1857,1881]" captionStart="FIGURE 17 a – e" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1733,1756]" captionTargetBox="[151,1428,193,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,193,1712]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 17 a – e. Megachile serrula. a. Female face. b. Female habitus. c. Male face. d. Male habitus. e. Male T 6 – T 7." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246142/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[390,418,1857,1881]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="17.0">17</number>
c–e
</figureCitation>
). Lengths: face 3.0 mm; scutum 2.0 mm; forewing 
<quantity box="[1045,1135,1857,1881]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
; body 
<quantity box="[1211,1315,1857,1881]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="12.5">12.5 mm</quantity>
. Structure. Clypeus slightly convex, ventral edge about straight, median tubercle; mandible three apical teeth, a large tooth on ventral edge; foretarsus unmodified; T 
<number box="[580,593,1929,1953]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="6.0">6</number>
with mediolongitudinal carina, distal edge serrate, convex (
<figureCitation box="[1261,1385,1929,1953]" captionStart="FIGURE 17 a – e" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1733,1756]" captionTargetBox="[151,1428,193,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,193,1712]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 17 a – e. Megachile serrula. a. Female face. b. Female habitus. c. Male face. d. Male habitus. e. Male T 6 – T 7." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246142/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[1313,1341,1929,1953]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="17.0">17</number>
d–e
</figureCitation>
); T 
<number box="[1423,1436,1930,1953]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="7.0">7</number>
with mediolongitudinal keel, pointed posteromedially (
<figureCitation box="[795,896,1965,1989]" captionStart="FIGURE 17 a – e" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1733,1756]" captionTargetBox="[151,1428,193,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,193,1712]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 17 a – e. Megachile serrula. a. Female face. b. Female habitus. c. Male face. d. Male habitus. e. Male T 6 – T 7." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246142/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[853,883,1965,1989]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="17.0">17</number>
e
</figureCitation>
); S 
<number box="[937,952,1965,1989]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="4.0">4</number>
concave posteromedially, with subapical carina; S 
<number box="[250,264,2001,2025]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="5.0">5</number>
distal edge straight; terminalia as in 
<taxonomicName box="[676,804,2002,2025]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Creightonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cognata">
<emphasis box="[676,804,2002,2025]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">M. cognata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[820,840,2001,2025]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">cf</emphasis>
. 
<figureCitation box="[854,961,2001,2025]" captionStart="FIGURE 2 a – f" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1844,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,517,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,517,1823]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2 a – f. Megachile cognata. a. Female mandible. b – f. Male. b. T 6. c. S 4. d. S 6. e. S 8. f. Genital capsule." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246127/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[906,920,2001,2025]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
d–f
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
